    public interface ICMLField
extends com.hazelcast.nio.serialization.DataSerializable
    A block/function in a control block diagram is represented in CML using a field of type ICMLField - the root interface of all CIM control block/function implementation. There two basic concepts: Block (StaticBlock and ControlBlock) and Function 1) Block is two-way, with only one input, which means you can find y from u and u(0) from y(0) 2) Function is only one way, with multiple inputs. You can only find y from a set of u(s). So function cannot put in the main path between RefPoint and Controller output
